## 4. ğŸš€ Runtime Verification Rule (Backend)
> **Mandatory Check**: Before marking a backend task as complete, you MUST verify that the application starts without runtime errors.
> 
> **Procedure:**
> 1. Start the dependent services (MySQL/Redis) using `docker-compose up -d`.
> 2. Attempt to start the Spring Boot application (or a minimal context test).
> 3. Check the logs for `ApplicationContext` startup errors or critical exceptions.
> 4. If an error occurs (e.g., Dependency Injection fail, DB connection fail), FIX IT before proceeding.
> 5. After verification, shut down the backend application to free up resources.
